





"""# 1️⃣ Stack
What is a Stack?:- A Stack is a data structure that follows: LIFO → Last In, First Out

Like a stack of plates 🍽
Put plate A
Put plate B
Put plate C

Exp: Stack of plates, Browser back button, Undo operations
When removing →
C comes first, then B, then A."""


"""
Call Stack (Very Important):- When a function runs, Python puts it into a special memory area called the Call Stack.

Each function call: Gets its own memory frame, Waits until it finishes, Then gets removed"""
# When you call a function in Python:
def greet():
    print("Hello")

greet()

# Now in recursion:
def fun(n):
    if n == 0:
         return
    fun(n-1)
fun(3)

"""Calling fun(3) creates stack:fun(3), fun(2), fun(1), fun(0)
Each function call waits until the next one finishes. That waiting memory area = Call Stack"""





def greet():
    print("Hello")

def main():
    greet()

main()
"""
main()  ← pushed
greet() ← pushed
greet() finishes → popped
main() finishes → popped
"""


"""2️⃣ Base Case:- 
Base Case = Stopping condition
Without it → infinite recursion → crash.
If you remove if n == 0 → it never stops. Base case = condition that stops recursion."""
def countdown(n):
    if n == 0:   # Base Case
        return
    print(n)
    countdown(n-1)  # Recursive Case

countdown(5)





